commit.message: CSharpLanguageServer.Handlers.Workspace: restore dynamic registration for DidChangeWatchedFiles
CSharpLanguageServer.Handlers.Initialization: wrap lspClient.ClientRegisterCapability with try/with and log the process

refactor: Lazily register capability

Before initialization of WorkspaceManager, we can't handle any requests.
However, client might send several time-consuming requests during the
period, e.g. `textDocument/codeLens`, `textDocument/semanticTokens/full`
and `textDocument/inlayHint`. Even if we send some error responses to
client (such as "Server is not ready"), client will retry the requests
soon.

Hence, layzily register the capabilities such that client will send the
requests to us during initialization.

CSharpLanguageServer.Handlers: import placeholer handlers from rework branch

Co-authored-by: Adam Tao <tcx4c70@gmail.com>
CSharpLanguageServer.Handlers.CodeAction: reduce logging noise
